column1: # Definition: The percentage of women aged 15-49 with a live birth in a given time period that received antenatal care four or more times as a percentage of women age 15-49 years with a live birth in a given time period. Available survey data on this indicator usually do not specify the type of the provider, therefore, in general, receipt of care by ANY provider is measured.
# Data from the No Ceilings project: http://noceilings.org
# For more about the data, please visit http://noceilings.org/data
